						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone near the temple of Rāmaliṅga.</hi></p>						

						<p>Ja[gattuṅga]—(Undated).</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary and damaged inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Ja[gattuṅga]</hi> and states that <hi rend="bold">Rājāditya</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Banavāsi Twelve-thousand</hi> and a certain <hi rend="bold">Māra</hi> was the <hi rend="italic">gāvuṇḍa.</hi> It seems to refer to some gift (Cf. No. 34 above. </p>						

						</summary>
